{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"usefulItems":"large bowl, cling wrap, springform pan (10 in.), kitchen towel, oven","id":"r175469","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-hqSvGI7-sz4\/XZaoKQSRqfI\/AAAAAAAAhHk\/CObjRHq1dVAYXyubXdDhus8fJmFtbAq4ACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_fxdJEuLS-ke1K7Rc.png","title":"Garlic Pull-Apart Knots","publishedAt":"2017-05-12T00:00:00Z","ingredients":[{"content":"1 oz olive oil, plus extra to grease"},{"content":"15 oz bread flour"},{"content":"2 ½ oz whole wheat flour"},{"content":"9 oz warm water (100°F-110°F)"},{"content":"½ oz sugar"},{"content":"2 ¼ tsp rapid rise yeast"},{"content":"3 tsp salt, divided"},{"content":"4 garlic cloves"},{"content":"½ oz fresh flat leaf parsley, leaves only (optional)"},{"content":"2 ½ oz unsalted butter"}],"nutrition":{"protein":"6 g","fat":"8 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"32 g","calories":"925 kJ \/ 221 kcal"},"preparations":[{"content":"Lightly grease a large bowl and a springform pan and set aside."},{"content":"Place bread flour, whole wheat flour, water, sugar, yeast, 1 oz oil and 2 tsp salt into mixing bowl and knead <b>2 min\/<b>."},{"content":"Form dough into a ball and transfer into prepared bowl. Cover with cling wrap and let dough rise until doubled in size (approx. 1 hr.)."},{"content":"Place garlic and parsley into mixing bowl and chop <b>5 sec\/speed 7<b>. Scrape down side of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add butter and 1 tsp salt and mix <b>30 sec\/speed 4<b>."},{"content":"Preheat oven to 350°F. Divide dough in half. Place each half onto a lightly floured surface. Evenly stretch each dough into a rectangle (approx. 9 in. x 12 in.), with lightly floured fingertips. Spread each with half the reserved garlic butter. Cut dough into 6 pieces (3 in. x 6 in.) and roll the dough so the garlic butter is wrapped in the center. Gently stretch the dough just enough to allow you to easily tie into a knot shape. Place into the springform pan. Repeat with remaining dough."},{"content":"Cover with a damp kitchen towel and set pan in a warm place until doubled in size (approx. 20 min.)."},{"content":"Bake for 35 minutes (350°F) or until golden. Serve warm."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Make in advance method: dough can be made in advance and stored in a refrigerator for up to 2 days. Remove dough from refrigerator and allow it to rise (approx. 1 hr.) before proceeding with the filling.","For a glazed or shiny look to your garlic knots, brush with olive oil or melted butter immediately before and after baking."],"basicInfo":["medium","15m","1h 55m","12 pieces"]}